news.title: Mumbai property market on record-setting spree, February scales over 10,000 registrations
news.para: Property registrations in Mumbai, the country’s biggest real estate market, have continued to reflect robust momentum in February, surpassing the pre-pandemic levels witnessed two years ago by a wide margin.

news.title: Startups to lease 29 million sq ft office space in 2022-24 in six cities: Report
news.para: The demand will be led by fintech and logistics startups as they have gained momentum post-pandemic due to increased digital adoption and e-commerce boom, Colliers India said in a statement.

news.title: Satellite images to help track projects, encroachments in Gurugram and Faridabad
news.para: The Gurugram Metropolitan Development Authority (GMDA) plans to use satellite images to track temporal changes in urban areas and on agricultural land in Gurgaon and Faridabad. Officials said that the system could help track development projects and encroachments in the two districts.

news.title: Maharashtra government increases FSI for slum-rehab projects across state
news.para: The government has revised the Unified Development Control Promotion Regulations (UDCPR) for the rest of the state to give effect to this increase in the FSI.

news.title: Karnataka: Realty sector wants guidance value, stamp duty slashed
news.para: Their demands include a reduction in property prices by slashing the guidance value, a fixed minimum selling price at which a property can be registered, and reduction in stamp duty for all residential properties irrespective of price tags.

news.title: Delhi: Businessman arrested for duping flat buyers of Rs 14 crore
news.para: The duo after taking money from people misappropriated it by diverting it to various group companies and projects, police said.

news.title: Kolkata: Pandemic leaves imprint on home buying, bigger flats remain in demand
news.para: While the largest pie of home sales comprised two-bedroom homes till 2019, the pandemic saw the home buyers willing to invest more to purchase bigger homes. Consequently, demand for three bedroom homes outstripped that of two-bedroom apartments in 2020. In 2021, demand for three-bedroom flats increased further. So did the sales of four-bedroom apartments.

news.title: Ghaziabad: GDA ready to hand over Indirapuram, but GMC won't take it until infra work is over
news.para: While the GDA says it is ready to hand over the township to the corporation, the GMC has contended that there are pending infrastructure development issues in the township and it can’t take over Indirapuram until they are resolved.

news.title: Pune civic body's gunthewari scheme off to slow start
news.para: BJP’s state president Chandrakant Patil said, “Regularisation charges for the proposals should be reduced. Relaxation is a must in the rules related to road widths to avail this scheme.”

news.title: Life Mission's final list extended again by Kerala government
news.para: ​​As per the latest order issued by the local self-government department (LSGD) on Friday, the finalization of the draft list (which was supposed to be published on Feb 28) has now been extended till April 16.

news.title: Supertech twin towers to be demolished by May 22: Noida authority to SC
news.para: Realty major Supertech Ltd February 28 informed the Supreme Court that the demolition of its twin 40-storey towers of its Emerald Court Project in Noida will be completed by May 22. The next hearing in the case is scheduled for May 17.

news.title: Centre won't include wrongly deleted Rajasthan PMAY-Gramin beneficiaries
news.para: In a letter written to the state on February 15, 2022, the ministry wrote, “Request cannot be agreed as the system rejects the beneficiaries on the basis of the records entered by the state at the time of Awaas+ survey.”

news.title: Chamarajanagar development body permitted to construct new layouts
news.para: The state government has given green signal to develop the new layout with modern facilities on a 50:50 partnership basis. This comes amid an unsuccessful attempt by its counterpart in Mysuru.

news.title: Guidebook on residential EV charging in Delhi to be launched on Monday
news.para: ​The document guides residential societies in understanding the importance of EV charging, details the processes involved in planning, installing and managing EV charging stations in the parking space of the societies, the statement on Sunday said.

news.title: Karnataka government plans new scheme to regularise revenue sites
news.para: Chief minister Basavaraj Bommai has held several rounds of talks with state urban department, rural development and panchayat raj, and BBMP officials regarding a scheme to regularise B khata sites in major municipal corporations.
